--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
python app.py --> Run the Application, used only for testing, not for production environment.
# NOTE: Open an other terminal of same server. After above command, not press "ctrl+C". And check ""curl http://localhost:5000/"" to check the output.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Install Gunicorn --> Production Grade Server
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
pip install gunicorn          --> installs gunicorn.
pip list                      --> Verify the installation.
pip freeze > requirements.txt --> updating the requirements.txt, as newdependency is added.

gunicorn --bind 0.0.0.0:5000 app:app --> Start the Application with Gunicorn
        "gunicorn"            --> Starts the Gunicorn server.
        "--bind 0.0.0.0:5000" --> Listens on all network interfaces on port 5000.
        "app:app"             --> because we have object called "app" in file of "app.py"
gunicorn --workers 3 app:app          --> If three users send requests at the same time. This increases concurrency.

curl http://localhost:5000/ --> to check the output.
http://13.234.xxx.xxx:5000/ --> Also accessable through public ip via browser.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The problem is that Gunicorn is directly exposed to the Internet, which isn't considered a best practice.
# NGINX comes into play here.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
sudo apt install nginx -y --> nginx installation
nginx -v -->verify installation.
sudo systemctl start nginx
sudo systemctl enable nginx
sudo systemctl status nginx

sudo vim /etc/nginx/sites-available/default --> Configure Nginx as a Reverse Proxy by replacing the existing content of file below content.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name _;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:5000;

        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
    }
}
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

sudo nginx -t --> Test the Configuration
sudo systemctl restart nginx --> restart nginx
gunicorn --workers 3 --bind 127.0.0.1:5000 app:app --> Start Gunicorn.
"http://13.234.xxx.xxx" --> now check this via browser.
